Peel the @carrot{1}, remove the top and bottom and then chop into roughly ½cm cubes. Make them as small as you can! Chop the @celery stick{1} into tiny cubes too. Remove the root and dark green tops from the @leek{1} and slice into ½cm rounds. Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, remove the seeds and finely chop as much as you dare!

Pinch the top of each @thyme{1/2%sprig} stalk in one hand and run thumb and index finger of the other downwards to strip off the leaves. Pick the @sage leaves{1/2%sprig} from their stalks and roughly chop. (Discard the stalks from both herbs.)

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the carrot, celery, leek, chilli, thyme and sage. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and cook gently until soft, about ~{8%minutes}.

> TIP: Turn the heat down if the ingredients start to brown.

Place each @British chicken breasts{2} between two sheets of #clingfilm{}. Whack with the bottom of a saucepan until just under 1cm thick all over. Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the chicken, skin-side down, and cook for around ~{5-6%minutes} on each side. Season with a pinch of salt and @black pepper{} whilst cooking.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Thoroughly rinse and drain the @green lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Add them to the pan of veggies with a splash of @water{}, the @chicken stock pot{1/2} and the @creme fraiche{1/2}. Add a few grinds of @black pepper{} (taste and add more if needed). Stir well and heat through until the lentils are piping hot.

Spoon the spicy lentils onto plates and top with your pan-fried chicken. Enjoy!